Copper and silver are non-toxic material and especially, Cu+ is a cheap and earth abundant one. The structure of A3BX6 was regulated by the ratio of elemental materials in the DMSO solution. Hence, CuI and BiI3 were mixed in 3:1 molar ratio to be Cu3BiI6. AgI and BiI3 were mixed in 3:1 molar ratio to be Ag3BiI6. In case of Ag3BiI3(SCN)3, AgSCN and BiI3 were mixed in 3:1 molar ratio. The XRD patterns of Ag3BiI6, Ag3BiI3(SCN)3 and Cu3BiI6 as casted films are shown in Fig. 6a. The film made by Ag3BiI6 signifies the trigonal structure with R 3¯\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
